node.text:
💙🌲 Incredible blues from the waters of the Canadian #RockyMountains.

If you've been following us for a while, you likely know that the vibrant #blue color of #Canadian lakes is due to rock flour in the water. Rock flour is produced by the movement of #glaciers or boulders that cause rock surfaces to grind against one another. Because the rock flour is very lightweight, it remains suspended in the water. This then scatters sunlight to produce that famous blue color, the same way dust in the atmosphere makes our skies look blue.

Credits: @mitch_explores.
